---
title: French Dip Chicken Sandwiches with Au Jus Sauce & Roasted Broccoli
description: Dip dip hooray! Celebrate dinnertime with a twist on this classic hot sammie. Our chefs swapped out the traditional roast beef and layered thin chicken cutlets, Monterey Jack, and fresh sliced tomato between buttery, toasted sourdough. Roasted carrot fries delight on the side and a light chicken broth au jus makes the perfect sandwich dipper. So dunk, soak, swirl, repeat—this French dip just can’t be beat.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/62cedb28dde8884ef608f8a2-e8cfecf9.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/french-dip-chicken-sandwiches-62cedb28dde8884ef608f8a2-2ab951f6.pdf
time required: 35 minutes
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/french-dip-chicken-sandwiches-62cedb28dde8884ef608f8a2
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 67 g
  sugar: 5 g
  protein: 45 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 970 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: North America
---

Adjust rack to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut
@butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) into four cubes (eight cubes for 4).
Place butter in a #small bowl{}; bring to room temperature.

Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} into sticks (like fries—ours were 3 inches
long and 1⁄3 inch thick). Thinly slice @tomato{1} into rounds.

> Cut broccoli florets into bite-size pieces if necessary. (Save carrots for
> another use.)

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp};
season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender,
~{15-20%minutes}.

> Swap in broccoli for carrots.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Place between
two pieces of #plastic wrap{} and pound with a #mallet{} or #heavy-bottomed pan{}
until 1⁄2 inch thick. Season all over with @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, salt, and
pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Reserve pan.

Heat pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @butter{1%tbsp} plain butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and @water{1/2%cup} (1 cup for 4). Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until heated through, ~{1-2%minutes} (2-4 minutes for 4). Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Turn off heat. Divide au jus sauce between two #small bowls{} (four bowls for 4);
set aside for serving. Wipe out pan.

On a clean work surface, spread softened butter onto one side of each
@sourdough bread{4%slices}. Place half the bread slices buttered sides down;
layer with @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, tomato, and chicken. Top with
remaining bread slices, buttered sides up.

Heat pan used for au jus over medium-high heat. Add sandwiches and toast
until lightly golden and cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Halve sandwiches on a diagonal.

Divide sandwiches and carrot fries between plates. Serve with au jus sauce for
dipping.